{"types":[{"section":"\n{{fr-verb}}\n\n# to [[admit]]; to [[agree]] {{+obj|fr|:de<to/upon>}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|'''convenir''' du prix de quelque chose|t=to '''agree''' on the price of something}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|Je '''conviens''' que c'est un problème.|t=I '''agree''' that it's a problem.}}\n# to [[suit]]; to be [[convenient]] for {{+obj|fr|:à<someone>}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|On se voit mardi, si cela '''convient''' aux autres.|We’ll meet up on Tuesday, if this '''suits''' the others.}}\n#* {{quote-book|fr|title=Géographie des Plantes|last=Gaussen|first=Henri|year=1933|publisher=Armand Colin|page=67|text=Il est bien évident que les plantes vivent uniquement dans les milieux qui leur '''conviennent'''{{...}}|t=It is obvious that plants live solely in the environments which '''suit''' them{{...}}}}\n# {{lb|fr|impersonal}} to be [[appropriate]] or [[admissible]] {{gloss|to be [[agreed]] upon according to convention}} {{+obj|fr|:de}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|Il ne me '''convient''' pas d’agir ainsi.|t=It would not '''suit''' me to act in that way.}}\n#* {{quote-book|fr|title=La Force des choses|last=De Beauvoir|first=Simone|year=1963|publisher=Éditions Gallimard|text=Les jeunes femmes ont un sens aigu de ce qu'il '''convient''' de faire et de ne pas faire quand on a cessé d'être jeune. « Je ne comprends pas, disent-elles, que passé quarante ans on se teigne en blond ; qu'on s'exhibe en bikini ; qu'on coquette avec les hommes. Moi, quand j'aurai cet âge-là... » |t=Young women have a sharp sense of what they '''should''' and should not do when they are no longer young. They say, \"I don't understand women over forty who dye their hair blonde, who show themselves off in bikinis and flirt with men. When ''I'' am that age...\"}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* When conjugating {{m|fr||convenir}}, compound tenses '''cannot''' be formed using {{m|fr|être}} as the [[auxiliary verb]] in the sense of “to suit”. It must take {{m|fr|avoir}}. This is even though it derives from {{m|fr|venir}}, which takes {{m|fr||être}}.\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{fr-conj-auto}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col2|fr\n|convenance\n|convention\n}}\n\n","alt":[],"syn":[],"type":"verb","forms":[{"mod":"inf","aux":["avoir","être"],"pronom":false,"impers":false}],"trans":["to agree","to admit","to agree .mw-parser-output .object-usage-tag{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output .deprecated{color:olivedrab}","to suit","to be convenient for","to be appropriate or admissible"],"group":3,"conj":[{"mod":"indc","tenses":[{"tense":"pres","forms":[["je conv","iens"],["tu conv","iens"],["il conv","ient"],["nous conv","enons"],["vous conv","enez"],["ils conv","iennent"]]},{"tense":"pass-c","forms":[["j'ai conv","enu"],["tu as conv","enu"],["il a conv","enu"],["nous avons conv","enu"],["vous avez conv","enu"],["ils ont conv","enu"]]},{"tense":"impf","forms":[["je conv","enais"],["tu conv","enais"],["il conv","enait"],["nous conv","enions"],["vous conv","eniez"],["ils conv","enaient"]]},{"tense":"pqpf","forms":[["j'avais conv","enu"],["tu avais conv","enu"],["il avait conv","enu"],["nous avions conv","enu"],["vous aviez conv","enu"],["ils avaient conv","enu"]]},{"tense":"pass-s","forms":[["je conv","ins"],["tu conv","ins"],["il conv","int"],["nous conv","înmes"],["vous conv","întes"],["ils conv","inrent"]]},{"tense":"pass-a","forms":[["j'eus conv","enu"],["tu eus conv","enu"],["il eut conv","enu"],["nous eûmes conv","enu"],["vous eûtes conv","enu"],["ils eurent conv","enu"]]},{"tense":"futr","forms":[["je conv","iendrai"],["tu conv","iendras"],["il conv","iendra"],["nous conv","iendrons"],["vous conv","iendrez"],["ils conv","iendront"]]},{"tense":"futr-a","forms":[["j'aurai conv","enu"],["tu auras conv","enu"],["il aura conv","enu"],["nous aurons conv","enu"],["vous aurez conv","enu"],["ils auront conv","enu"]]}]},{"mod":"subj","tenses":[{"tense":"subj-pr","forms":[["que je conv","ienne"],["que tu conv","iennes"],["qu'il conv","ienne"],["que nous conv","enions"],["que vous conv","eniez"],["qu'ils conv","iennent"]]},{"tense":"subj-ps","forms":[["que j'aie conv","enu"],["que tu aies conv","enu"],["qu'il ait conv","enu"],["que nous ayons conv","enu"],["que vous ayez conv","enu"],["qu'ils aient conv","enu"]]},{"tense":"subj-im","forms":[["que je conv","insse"],["que tu conv","insses"],["qu'il conv","înt"],["que nous conv","inssions"],["que vous conv","inssiez"],["qu'ils conv","inssent"]]},{"tense":"subj-pq","forms":[["que j'eusse conv","enu"],["que tu eusses conv","enu"],["qu'il eût conv","enu"],["que nous eussions conv","enu"],["que vous eussiez conv","enu"],["qu'ils eussent conv","enu"]]}]},{"mod":"cond","tenses":[{"tense":"cond-pr","forms":[["je conv","iendrais"],["tu conv","iendrais"],["il conv","iendrait"],["nous conv","iendrions"],["vous conv","iendriez"],["ils conv","iendraient"]]},{"tense":"cond-pp","forms":[["j'aurais conv","enu"],["tu aurais conv","enu"],["il aurait conv","enu"],["nous aurions conv","enu"],["vous auriez conv","enu"],["ils auraient conv","enu"]]},{"tense":"cond-pd","forms":[["j'eusse conv","enu"],["tu eusses conv","enu"],["il eût conv","enu"],["nous eussions conv","enu"],["vous eussiez conv","enu"],["ils eussent conv","enu"]]}]},{"mod":"impr","tenses":[{"tense":"impr-pr","forms":[["conv","iens"],["conv","enons"],["conv","enez"]]},{"tense":"impr-ps","forms":[["aie conv","enu"],["ayons conv","enu"],["ayez conv","enu"]]}]},{"mod":"part","tenses":[{"tense":"part-pr","forms":[["conv","enant"]]},{"tense":"part-ps","forms":[["conv","enu"],["conv","enue"],["conv","enus"],["conv","enues"],["ayant conv","enu"]]}]},{"mod":"inf","tenses":[{"tense":"inf-pr","forms":[["convenir"]]},{"tense":"inf-ps","forms":[["avoir conv","enu"]]}]},{"mod":"gern","tenses":[{"tense":"gern-pr","forms":[["en conv","enant"]]},{"tense":"gern-ps","forms":[["en ayant conv","enu"]]}]}],"preps":[{"rel":"v-tr-i","prep":"à","ex":"cela convient à son âge; cela convient à Pierre"},{"rel":"v-tr-i","prep":"avec","ex":"convenir avec son ami de qqch."},{"rel":"v-tr-i","prep":"de","ex":"convenir de sa méprise; convenir de voyager; convenir des conditions"},{"rel":"v-tr-i","prep":"entre","ex":"ils ont convenu entre eux du lieu de leur rencontre"}],"tags":["freq","intrans","transit"],"html":"<p><span class=\"headword-line\"><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"fr\">convenir</strong></span>\n</p><ol><li>to <a href=\"/wiki/admit\" title=\"admit\">admit</a>; to <a href=\"/wiki/agree\" title=\"agree\">agree</a> <style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r80655919\">.mw-parser-output .object-usage-tag{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output .deprecated{color:olivedrab}</style>[<i>with</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/de#French\" title=\"de\">de</a></b> <small>‘to/upon’</small>]\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\"><b>convenir</b> du prix de quelque chose</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">to <b>agree</b> on the price of something</span></span></dd>\n<dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Je <b>conviens</b> que c'est un problème.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">I <b>agree</b> that it's a problem.</span></span></dd></dl></li>\n<li>to <a href=\"/wiki/suit\" title=\"suit\">suit</a>; to be <a href=\"/wiki/convenient\" title=\"convenient\">convenient</a> for <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r80655919\">[<i>with</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/%C3%A0#French\" title=\"à\">à</a></b> <small>‘someone’</small>]\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">On se voit mardi, si cela <b>convient</b> aux autres.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">We’ll meet up on Tuesday, if this <b>suits</b> the others.</span></span></dd></dl>\n<ul><li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\"><b>1933</b></span>, Henri Gaussen, <cite>Géographie des Plantes</cite>, Armand Colin, page <span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\">67</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation cited-passage\" lang=\"fr\">Il est bien évident que les plantes vivent uniquement dans les milieux qui leur <b>conviennent</b><span class=\"q-hellip-sp\"> </span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\">[</span>…<span class=\"q-hellip-b\">]</span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\"></span></span><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">It is obvious that plants live solely in the environments which <b>suit</b> them<span class=\"q-hellip-sp\"> </span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\">[</span>…<span class=\"q-hellip-b\">]</span><span class=\"q-hellip-b\"> </span></span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>\n<li><span class=\"usage-label-sense\"><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content label-content\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#impersonal\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">impersonal</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">)</span></span> to be <a href=\"/wiki/appropriate\" title=\"appropriate\">appropriate</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/admissible\" title=\"admissible\">admissible</a> <span class=\"mention-gloss-paren\">(</span><span class=\"mention-gloss\">to be <a href=\"/wiki/agreed#English\" title=\"agreed\">agreed</a> upon according to convention</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-paren\">)</span> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r80655919\">[<i>with</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/de#French\" title=\"de\">de</a></b>]\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Il ne me <b>convient</b> pas d’agir ainsi.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">It would not <b>suit</b> me to act in that way.</span></span></dd></dl>\n<ul><li><div class=\"citation-whole\"><span class=\"cited-source\"><span class=\"None\" lang=\"und\"><b>1963</b></span>, Simone De Beauvoir, <cite>La Force des choses</cite>, Éditions Gallimard:</span><dl><dd><div class=\"h-quotation\"><span class=\"Latn e-quotation cited-passage\" lang=\"fr\">Les jeunes femmes ont un sens aigu de ce qu'il <b>convient</b> de faire et de ne pas faire quand on a cessé d'être jeune. «&nbsp;Je ne comprends pas, disent-elles, que passé quarante ans on se teigne en blond ; qu'on s'exhibe en bikini ; qu'on coquette avec les hommes. Moi, quand j'aurai cet âge-là...&nbsp;»</span><dl><dd><span class=\"e-translation\">Young women have a sharp sense of what they <b>should</b> and should not do when they are no longer young. They say, \"I don't understand women over forty who dye their hair blonde, who show themselves off in bikinis and flirt with men. When <i>I</i> am that age...\"</span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li></ol><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Usage_notes\">Usage notes</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=convenir&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14\" title=\"Edit section: Usage notes\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><ul><li>When conjugating <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\">convenir</i>, compound tenses <b>cannot</b> be formed using <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/%C3%AAtre#French\" title=\"être\">être</a></i> as the <a href=\"/wiki/auxiliary_verb\" title=\"auxiliary verb\">auxiliary verb</a> in the sense of “to suit”. It must take <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir#French\" title=\"avoir\">avoir</a></i>. This is even though it derives from <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/venir#French\" title=\"venir\">venir</a></i>, which takes <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\">être</i>.</li></ul><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Conjugation_2\">Conjugation</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=convenir&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15\" title=\"Edit section: Conjugation\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Related_terms_2\">Related terms</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=convenir&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16\" title=\"Edit section: Related terms\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><div class=\"list-switcher-wrapper\"><div class=\"term-list columns-bg\"><ul><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/convenance#French\" title=\"convenance\">convenance</a></span></li><li><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/convention#French\" title=\"convention\">convention</a></span></li></ul></div></div>"}],"title":"convenir","id":"461975","audios":[{"name":"Fr-convenir.ogg","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/df/Fr-convenir.ogg"}],"ipas":["/kɔ̃v.niʁ/"],"pronunSection":"\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-convenir.ogg}}\n\n","pronunHtml":"<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:French_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:French pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/kɔ̃v.niʁ/</span></li>\n<li><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r50165410\">.mw-parser-output .k-player .k-attribution{visibility:hidden}</style><table class=\"audiotable\" style=\"\"><tbody><tr><td>Audio<span class=\"ib-colon qualifier-colon\">:</span></td><td class=\"audiofile\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><span><audio id=\"mwe_player_0\" controls=\"\" preload=\"none\" data-mw-tmh=\"\" class=\"mw-file-element\" width=\"175\" style=\"\" data-durationhint=\"2\" data-mwtitle=\"Fr-convenir.ogg\" data-mwprovider=\"wikimediacommons\"><source src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/df/Fr-convenir.ogg\" type=\"audio/ogg; codecs=&quot;vorbis&quot;\" data-width=\"0\" data-height=\"0\"><source src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/d/df/Fr-conve